1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
Let's discuss some basic WordPress settings.

2
00:00:05,240 --> 00:00:08,240
As you embark on your WordPress website journey, you'll discover a range of options located

3
00:00:10,220 --> 00:00:13,220
under "Settings" at the bottom left of your dashboard.

4
00:00:13,740 --> 00:00:16,740
We will delve deeper into these options at a later stage, but let's focus on a few key

5
00:00:18,920 --> 00:00:21,920
settings to get your site up and running smoothly.

6
00:00:22,940 --> 00:00:25,940
The learning outcomes are, setting your site title and tagline, updating your site's time

7
00:00:28,880 --> 00:00:31,880
zone and choosing your homepage display.

8
00:00:33,640 --> 00:00:36,640
First up, let's talk about your site's identity.

9
00:00:36,920 --> 00:00:39,920
In the settings menu, you'll find "General".

10
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:43,120
These elements are not just for show.

11
00:00:42,240 --> 00:00:45,240
They play a vital role in how your site appears in search engine results.

12
00:00:46,400 --> 00:00:49,400
So what can you do?

13
00:00:48,320 --> 00:00:51,320
Craft a compelling title and tagline that not only represents your site but also entices

14
00:00:53,320 --> 00:00:56,320
visitors to open your site when they see it listed on search engines or when they visit

15
00:00:57,720 --> 00:01:00,720
your site.

16
00:00:59,960 --> 00:01:02,960
The site title and tagline should tell visitors what your site is about and who you are trying

17
00:01:04,880 --> 00:01:07,880
to attract.

18
00:01:06,200 --> 00:01:09,200
They are often among the first things visitors will notice on your site.

19
00:01:10,920 --> 00:01:13,920
The title is usually the name of your site, while the tagline is a short phrase or sentence

20
00:01:16,800 --> 00:01:19,800
that aims to communicate the site's main focus.

21
00:01:20,960 --> 00:01:23,960
Please note, you can choose not to display your tagline, but as mentioned, search engines

22
00:01:25,840 --> 00:01:28,840
pay attention to titles and taglines, which will also help you improve your site's SEO.

23
00:01:32,080 --> 00:01:35,080
So remember to add your tagline even though you might decide not to display it on the

24
00:01:36,360 --> 00:01:39,360
front end of your site.

25
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:41,880
Here is an example from a search engine where you don't see the tagline on the site, but

26
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:46,400
when you search for Mantis Research, you will see the site title, Mantis Research and part

27
00:01:50,080 --> 00:01:53,080
of the tagline, helping marketers publish research that gets attention.

28
00:01:54,080 --> 00:01:57,080
You can change your site's title and tagline below General settings, as shown in the example

29
00:02:02,320 --> 00:02:05,320
here.

30
00:02:04,240 --> 00:02:07,240
You can also update your site title and tagline within the Site Editor when updating your

31
00:02:09,920 --> 00:02:12,920
header for example.

32
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:14,600
If you update or change the Site Title block or the Site Tagline block, it will also update

33
00:02:17,320 --> 00:02:20,320
automatically below the General settings.

34
00:02:20,320 --> 00:02:23,320
Next, let's discuss the time zone settings below general.

35
00:02:26,480 --> 00:02:29,480
It is best if your site's time zone matches the time zone settings on your computer or

36
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:34,400
local time.

37
00:02:32,840 --> 00:02:35,840
It ensures that your scheduled posts go live at the right time, and if you post content

38
00:02:38,520 --> 00:02:41,520
ahead of time, you'll know exactly when it will be published.

39
00:02:44,040 --> 00:02:47,040
You also have the option to select your own date format, as well as time format.

40
00:02:51,360 --> 00:02:54,360
And you can even decide when you want your week to start.

41
00:02:56,440 --> 00:02:59,440
Now, let's focus on the structure of your website.

42
00:03:01,920 --> 00:03:04,920
In Reading, Under settings, you have the power to decide what visitors see when they land

43
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:09,720
on your site.

44
00:03:07,720 --> 00:03:10,720
Do you want a dynamic homepage that showcases your latest posts, or perhaps a static page?

45
00:03:14,000 --> 00:03:17,000
The choice is yours.

46
00:03:15,760 --> 00:03:18,760
By default WordPress displays a list of posts on the homepage of your site.

47
00:03:21,960 --> 00:03:24,960
This list of posts is automatically updated as soon as new posts are published.

48
00:03:27,360 --> 00:03:30,360
Also, there is no need to create any page to have a homepage with your latest posts.

49
00:03:35,040 --> 00:03:38,040
You might be asking, so where do I edit this homepage that displays my latest posts?

50
00:03:41,400 --> 00:03:44,400
This homepage is displayed via your blog home template.

51
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,880
So, if you have selected your latest posts as your homepage display, you can make your

52
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:54,080
way to Appearance and click on Editor.

53
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:56,960
This will open up your Site Editor, and on the right, by default, your blog home template

54
00:03:59,440 --> 00:04:02,440
will appear.

55
00:04:00,440 --> 00:04:03,440
To open it up, merely click on it, and now you can start editing your homepage template

56
00:04:06,560 --> 00:04:09,560
that displays your posts via the Query Loop block.

57
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:14,000
You can edit and customize your homepage right here.

58
00:04:18,440 --> 00:04:21,440
But if you prefer to have a static homepage, you can go ahead and make your way to pages,

59
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:27,240
and then create a homepage, as well as a page for posts, in this case my blog page.

60
00:04:34,000 --> 00:04:37,000
And then you can go ahead and create any other pages that you want on your site.

61
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:42,320
You can head back to the dashboard, select Settings, Reading, and then next to your homepage

62
00:04:45,680 --> 00:04:48,680
displays, activate using a static page.

63
00:04:49,760 --> 00:04:52,760
And then select one of the pages you created as your homepage or front page, and then below

64
00:04:55,520 --> 00:04:58,520
that, you can also select another page to display your dynamic posts or blog, for example.

65
00:05:02,800 --> 00:05:05,800
When you select a static page, your homepage will automatically be assigned to the default

66
00:05:07,920 --> 00:05:10,920
page template.

67
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:12,520
Let's make our way to pages to see this in action.

68
00:05:14,400 --> 00:05:17,400
When I open my static homepage, and then open up my setting sidebar, we will notice, on

69
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:24,360
the right, next to template, it says that this page has been assigned to the page template

70
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:30,000
or the default template.

71
00:05:30,640 --> 00:05:33,640
That means that your static homepage and other pages that have been assigned to this

72
00:05:35,760 --> 00:05:38,760
default template will share the same template, or in other words, the same header and footer.

73
00:05:41,720 --> 00:05:44,720
So if you wanted to update the header and the footer and the structure for this page,

74
00:05:46,080 --> 00:05:49,080
you do it in the template.

75
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:51,440
But you of course head back to your homepage to start adding content and building your

76
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:56,520
homepage from here using blocks.

77
00:05:59,560 --> 00:06:02,560
And when you edit your posts page, you will notice at the top it says you are currently

78
00:06:04,480 --> 00:06:07,480
editing the page that shows your latest posts.

79
00:06:08,320 --> 00:06:11,320
And once again, your blog page has been assigned to the blog home template.

80
00:06:14,080 --> 00:06:17,080
And please take note, you will build your entire blog page within the blog home template

81
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:22,600
and leave this page empty.

82
00:06:22,680 --> 00:06:25,680
Configuring the basic WordPress settings correctly is essential for your site's functionality

83
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:30,560
and appearance.

84
00:06:29,200 --> 00:06:32,200
And as mentioned, we will look at more settings further down the line.

